			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/01c3d7eac712432d73dbb0c2ed77506a?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/01c3d7eac712432d73dbb0c2ed77506a?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name"><a href="http://www.cynicologist.com/" class="comment-author-link" rel="external nofollow" itemprop="url">Orun Bhuiyan</a></span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-04-12T11:45:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2013/04/mass-wordpress-brute-force-attacks-myth-or-reality.html#comment-2560">April 12, 2013</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Block them.<br />
Or limit maximum login attempts in a time period using a plugin.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="comment-2570">
	<article >

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo avatar-default' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name"><a href="http://twitter.com/absurd_human" class="comment-author-link" rel="external nofollow" itemprop="url">Absurd Human</a></span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-04-12T15:04:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2013/04/mass-wordpress-brute-force-attacks-myth-or-reality.html#comment-2570">April 12, 2013</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Limit Login Attempts will not work &#8211; they are using far too many IPs, usually one login per IP per account. Best way is to .htaccess block attempts to POST to wp-login.php without the HTTP_REFERER being your domain.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

