		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3eed0f1cc2acdf8c02a9182d237095b3?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3eed0f1cc2acdf8c02a9182d237095b3?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name">Sherra Scott</span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-05-11T13:15:00-07:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2013/04/mass-wordpress-brute-force-attacks-myth-or-reality.html#comment-2598">May 11, 2013</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Create a new admin user (you will have to use different email address), log out of WordPress, log in as the new user, delete the old &#8220;admin&#8221; user, make the new user the author of all the old posts (WordPress will ask you to do this when you attempt to delete the old user), go into your settings and change your email address back to the old admin email addresses. Done.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment odd alt depth-3" id="comment-2600">
	<article >

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1b75467b058c401da64f39f3674444b6?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1b75467b058c401da64f39f3674444b6?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name">Bas van Zuilen</span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-12-31T08:36:00-08:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2013/04/mass-wordpress-brute-force-attacks-myth-or-reality.html#comment-2600">December 31, 2013</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Actually there are plugins voor wordpress that you can install that will allow you to change the adminstrator password, without having to create a new one and deleting the old.</p>
<p>Admin renamer extended is an example that I use, but there might be more.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
